						<summary>

						<p>On a pedestal of a lost image preserved in the village <hi rend="italic">chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a Jaina temple at Kalikeṟe and the installation of the image of Pārśvanātha therein for the preceptor Sakaḷachandra-bhaṭṭāraka by Hāli gāvuṇḍa, disciple of Bhānukīrtti-Siddhāntidēva of <hi rend="italic">Mūla-saṁgha, Koṇḍakundānvaya, Krāṇūr-gaṇa</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Tintriṇī-gachchha.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
